WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:03.920
If you're looking at interactive dashboard tools for Python, Shiny for Python and Streamlit

00:00:03.920 --> 00:00:06.480
come up a lot and I'm here to tell you the three differences between them.

00:00:06.480 --> 00:00:11.040
First one is Shiny's reactive execution means that the elements are minimally re-rendered.

00:00:11.040 --> 00:00:14.560
The second key difference is you can build relatively large Shiny applications

00:00:14.560 --> 00:00:18.879
without manually managing the application state or caching data either.

00:00:18.879 --> 00:00:21.280
And the third key difference is Shiny for Python allows you to

00:00:21.280 --> 00:00:24.719
customize the look and feel of your app in a way that Streamlit doesn't.

00:00:24.799 --> 00:00:30.400
Shiny for Python is designed to let you grow your app without extensively rewriting your code.

00:00:30.400 --> 00:00:33.840
So basically the patterns that you learn when developing a simple app

00:00:33.840 --> 00:00:37.040
should be robust enough to help you when you're making a complicated one.

00:00:37.040 --> 00:00:38.160
Hope that helps.

